    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nIn the cython3 we have changed the default logic to propagate exceptions by default. Consider following code:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\nfrom libc.stdlib cimport malloc\r\n\r\ncdef void *safe_alloc(size_t size):\r\n    mem =  malloc(size)\r\n    if mem is NULL:\r\n        raise MemoryError\r\n    return mem\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    cdef void *mem = NULL\r\n    try:\r\n        mem = safe_alloc(5)\r\n    except MemoryError:\r\n        print('Allocation of the memory failed.')\r\n```\r\n\r\nCalling `safe_alloc()` is by default causing calling `PyErr_Occurred()` after every call - see generated C code:\r\n```c\r\n__pyx_t_4 = __pyx_f_9exception_safe_alloc(5); if (unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) __PYX_ERR(0, 12, __pyx_L3_error)\r\n```\r\nThis can be dangerous when used together with `nogil` keyword - see notes in [1]\r\n\r\n\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nTo avoid unnecessary overhead we can propagate the exception via `NULL` value (same as `except? NULL`) when the function returns the pointer - the same is done when python object is returned - see notes in [1].\r\n\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\nWe can leave it as it is but I think it is unnecessary complication for the users.\n\n### Additional context\n\n[1] https://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/userguide/language_basics.html#error-return-values",
